.TH BABYLINE 1 "" "" "babyline manual"
.SH NAME
babyline \- a small Zig CLI demo
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B babyline
.I command
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
A small Zig CLI demo with subcommands, persistent config, and shell completion.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B hello
Greet someone.
Required: \-g, \-\-greeting
Optional: \-n, \-\-name
.TP
.B help
Show this help message.
.TP
.B user:create
Create a user.
Required: \-u, \-\-username
.TP
.B user:list
List users.
.TP
.B config:set
Set a config value.
Required: \-k, \-\-key, \-v, \-\-value
.TP
.B config:get
Get a config value.
Required: \-k, \-\-key
.TP
.B config:list
List all config values.
.TP
.B config:delete
Delete a config value.
Required: \-k, \-\-key
.TP
.B process
Run a ~5s spinner demo.
.TP
.B interactive
Launch arrow-key driven menu.
.TP
.B completion <bash|zsh|fish>
Generate a shell completion script.
.TP
.B docs <markdown|man|text|all>
Generate usage documentation.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-name
Name to greet
.TP
.BR \-g ", " \-\-greeting
Greeting word
.TP
.BR \-u ", " \-\-username
Username
.TP
.BR \-k ", " \-\-key
Config key
.TP
.BR \-v ", " \-\-value
Config value
